This article first appeared at southern weekend and is not to be reprinted without permission

By Wang Tao, southern weekly reporter

Editor in chief | Cao Haidong

During the New Year's Day just hatched chicks, feathers have not yet developed, curled up in the greenhouse. Yi Zhonghua is worried about them day by day in grow up, even moved to bury the mind of these small life.

Yi Zhonghua is a farmer in Zhijiang, Yichang City, Hubei province, who raises 6,000 chickens. The chicks hatched after an outbreak of COVID-19 pneumonia in Wuhan, the provincial capital, 400 km away. As of January 30,2020, a total of 7,711 confirmed cases had been reported in 31 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, exceeding the number of confirmed SARS cases in 2003.

More research is needed on whether the COVID-19 originated in the south China Seafood Market in Wuhan, but on Jan. 26, the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention tested that, of the 22 stalls and a garbage truck found at the south China Seafood Market in Wuhan, 93.9 percent of the positive specimens were found in the western district of the market, where there had been several wildlife trading shops, said COVID-19, a spokesman for the market.

It is in this context that the national ban on wildlife trade, many places also began to ban the sale of live poultry. Trade was suspended, live poultry could not be sold, and farmers were worried when roads were closed and feed could not be brought in.

According to the original plan, Yi Zhonghua's chicks will be released four and a half months after they hatch. But now they are little gold-swallowing beasts, ready to eat their food. Yi Zhonghua does not know when the epidemic can be stable, he worries that his farm can not support the chicken out, up to the 15th day of the first month.

On January 30,2020, the Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas, the Ministry of Ministry of Transport of the People's Republic of China and the Ministry of Public Security issued an emergency notice demanding that the normal circulation order of "vegetable basket" products and agricultural Means of production be ensured and the "green passage" system be strictly enforced.

Even if the feed gets in, the live chickens can't be sold. Front-line farmers may not have noticed a different policy a year ago. In April 2018, the Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas announced that it would encourage livestock and poultry breeding, slaughtering and processing enterprises to implement a model of "large-scale breeding, centralized slaughtering, cold-chain transportation and cold listing, " in order to strengthen supervision of livestock and Poultry Movement and epidemic prevention.

At present, the COVID-19 pneumonia outbreak may further promote the transformation of livestock and poultry slaughter model, consumers may be difficult to choose in the market in the future live poultry, now slaughter.

However, the first-line farmers do not seem to be ready, for the price of centralized acquisition, also do not know.

1
Feed will last until the 15th of the first month

1

###Feed will last until the 15th of the first month

Following the deployment of the Hubei provincial government's Level II emergency response to public health emergencies, the Hubei Provincial Market Supervision Bureau's measures on January 22 included a ban on the sale of live poultry, photos of the notification letters sent to farmers have also been scattered on wechat groups in Yichang.

Not only Hubei, but also Jiangsu, Chongqing, Henan, Ningxia and many other places have banned the trade, according to a search by southern weekend reporters.

In addition to the suspension of live poultry trading, the immediate difficulty for farmers is the shortage of feed. In addition to the 6,000 chickens, the 5,000 free-range chickens in Yi Zhonghua's family have also grown up. The 10,000-odd mouths eat about 2,000 yuan a day.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The family's 5,000 free-range chickens have grown up and are in dire need of release. (photo / Photo by Yi Zhonghua)

Poultry feed, including corn and processing feed, because of large land, short shelf life, in general, the farm only half a month of feed, there are feed factory salesman home delivery. In view of the Spring Festival during the feed factory holiday, farmers will save some more, but at most to the 15th day of the first month.

On the second day of the Lunar New Year, Chen Weidong, head of the SIYUNGUI farming cooperative in Yiling District, Yichang, realized that the market was not right. He went for a drive around the block and found that there were road closures, seven or eight times for 30 kilometers. Some of the junctions were paved with Earth, some with big stones, some with broken-down cars.

After the outbreak, in addition to the urban area "closed" traffic, the countryside has also been closed road, "now please eat the meal is Hongmen banquet" , "today go around, tomorrow pneumonia door" and other banners all over the sky. These measures effectively blocked the flow of people, but also to a certain extent affected the transport of feed.

On the afternoon of January 29, southern weekly called a salesman at a feed factory in Yichang. The salesman said he was not working yet, but the stock was enough to last a month. As for the traffic problem, he said a green pass might be needed.

How do I get a license? Southern weekend reporter as a farmer consulted the Yichang Transportation Bureau, the Transportation Bureau proposed to consult the Yichang Health Commission, a health commission staff said, freight, traffic police should be allowed to pass. The traffic bureau then replied that they could call 110 to ask if the traffic police would let them through.

Chen is not worried about green passes. He worries that raw materials for feed factories come from all over the country. Some may even have to pull corn from the northeast. When the stock of feed factories runs out, they may have to process and produce new feed without raw materials. Chen Weidong hurried to the farmers market to find a store selling corn, "corn must give me to keep. ".

Yichang isn't the only place with a problem transporting feed. On January 26,2020, the red-stamped document of the Huangmei County Agricultural and Rural Bureau of Huanggang City, Hubei Province, "instructions on slaughterhouses, feedlot transportation and products going out" was posted on the wechat public account "smart chicken" , the document proposed to the county prevention and Control Work Headquarters, the implementation of green channels, to ensure the normal production of animals in custody, maintain social stability.

On the afternoon of January 29, the Huangmei County Bureau of Agriculture and Rural Affairs replied to the southern weekend reporters that their request had been typed in and quickly approved by the headquarters. According to the director of the bureau, Li Yajun, dozens of them can be processed every day, most of them carrying feed and eggs. Villagers can quickly get green passage according to this process: The village has issued a certificate that local farms need feed, then to the township, agricultural and Rural Bureau, Emergency Command level approval. "We can do it with someone in our office, " Li Yajun said.

2
If we don't sell the chickens, the funding chain will be cut off

2

###If we don't sell the chickens, the funding chain will be cut off

Learned that the urgent need for feed can be resolved, Yi Zhonghua or not happy up, "feed by money can always be resolved, but the chicken is afraid to sell. ".

Since 2017, Yi has raised pigs and chickens at the same time. In 2019, when African swine fever was rampant, he switched to raising chickens entirely. "The impact of African swine fever has not yet caught up with him, " he said.

On weekdays, Yi's chickens are sold to restaurant or market owners. This Spring Festival, his hands of this batch of chickens had been sold late.

Different breeds of chickens come out at different times and at different prices. For example, white-feathered chickens take 42 days, while Yi's takes 41 / 2 months. Taken together, the cost of a chicken is around 4.5 yuan per kilo. In 2019, affected by African swine fever, the number of chicken farmers soared. In June 2019, the price of chicks in hatcheries doubled. During the National Day holiday, Yi Zhonghua's chickens sold for 13 yuan per catty.

But on the eve of the Spring Festival, the supply of this batch of adult chickens outstripped the demand, and the market was slow. "My chickens can only sell for 9 yuan per catty, and maybe 1.6 yuan for the white-feathered ones, " Yi recalled. "But there is no market for them. They can't be sold at all. "

Selling a wave of chickens into a stage, as a feed and a chicken to feel like a mortgage, this is the farmer's business model. According to the situation in 2020, Chen Weidong estimated that most of the farmers are prepared to feed the twenty-five Twelfth Lunar Month, the third day began selling chickens, the eighth day of the eighth feed factory to work, and then buy new feed. "Ten thousand chickens, one hundred and one thousand sold, half a month can be sold out. " But on the fifth day, he turned in the market, found that almost no one to buy food.

Yi Zhonghua is worried, chicken again can not sell out, capital chain may break. In addition, he is more worried about the sales model has changed, if late everyone is anxious to sell chicken, Slaughterhouse Unified Acquisition, underpricing, do not know how much to lose.

On January 29, southern weekend contacted a slaughterhouse in Yichang. The man said he had not been to work yet and had to wait for a unified government notice and hung up hurriedly.

The chicken is fresh and ready to be butchered. However, the long-distance transportation and storage of live poultry are easy to bring the risk of disease, the implementation of the deployment of the Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas, all over the promotion of centralized slaughter.

In July 2019, the city agricultural and Rural Bureau, the Market Supervision Bureau, the economic and Credit Bureau, the Urban Management Bureau and other departments were united, according to a news report posted on the website of Zhijiang City Government, where Yi is based, the city to ban the trade in live poultry slaughtering campaign, Zhijiang live poultry centralized slaughter quarantine, cold-chain distribution, Baitiao listed poultry meat supply model in full shape. The aim is to "strengthen the supervision of livestock and poultry slaughtering industry, reduce the risk of epidemic disease spread. ".

According to Li Yajun, Huangmei County Huanggang is going to set up a centralized slaughterhouse, the construction of the original plan, is now moving forward, than private slaughter, environmental protection, sanitary conditions will be better. On the question of whether slaughterhouses will underprice, he said, "It depends on market rules, people's demand and leverage conditions. There is always a way to operate, and the government will protect people's interests. "

In addition to concerns about underpricing by slaughterhouses, another concern of Yi Zhonghua is that the suspension of live poultry trading will send a strong signal to consumers, "I dare not buy chicken any more, especially in the neighboring provinces. Can chickens, ducks and geese infect or carry this (new type of coronavirus) virus? " Yi asked for an expert to point it out, "there can be no equivocation. ".

Breeders are predicting that there will be no breeders willing to incubate chickens any more. If there are no live chickens on the market in 2-3 months, the price of chicken will go up, but the question now is whether they can hold out until that day. Yi Zhonghua is a little disheartened, no longer want to engage in breeding, want to go out to work. But where will the 44-year-old work?
